      "id": "inference_boundary_compliance",
      "name": "Inference Boundary Compliance",
      "question": "Does the memory item avoid making inferences that go beyond what is stated? Specifically, does it avoid inferring internal states, causation, or character traits that were not explicitly stated?",
      "why_it_matters": "While some inference is necessary, crossing into unsupported psychological attribution or causal reasoning distorts the source and misleads future users.",
      "failure_examples": [
        "Memory item states 'Alice was frustrated because her manager was demanding' when the conversation only shows the manager made a request with no emotional attribution",
        "Memory item states 'Bob decided to quit his job due to burnout' when the conversation only mentions he 'has been tired lately'"
      ],
      "source_trace": [
