      "id": "relationship_accuracy",
      "name": "Relationship Accuracy",
      "question": "Are the relationships between entities accurate according to the conversation? Does the memory avoid misrepresenting familial, professional, or social relationships?",
      "why_it_matters": "Relationship errors can fundamentally misrepresent the social structure and context of the conversation.",
      "failure_examples": [
        "Memory item states 'Carol is David's wife' when the conversation establishes Carol as David's sister",
        "Memory item states 'Alice works for Bob' when the conversation shows they are both employed by the same company with no direct reporting relationship"
